The Director General of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC), Brigadier General Shuaibu Ibrahim has said that he is hopeful that the Corps member, Value Eromosele Akhigbe, who went missing in December, 2018, while serving in Plateau state will be found. Speaking when he visited the family of the corps member in Uromi, Edo State on Friday, he said the scheme was working with security agencies to make sure the young man was found. “Mummy, I have spoken with you on phone severally, giving you assurances that we are doing everything possible to locate Value, and I am here physically to reassure you and members of your family that we are working round the clock with all security agencies to find him. I want you to remain calm and be hopeful because, I m hopeful that we shall find our missing son. When that happens, I promise to bring him to you personally,” he assured. Mother of the missing Corps member, Mrs. Dora Akhigbe appealed to government to deploy all measures to find her son. Earlier, Jerry Akhigbe who is an elder brother to Value received the NYSC boss at Auchi and led him to Uromi. He appreciated NYSC on behalf of the family for the concern it has shown over the ugly situation. NYSC DG visits family of Late Precious, says he died a hero NYSC Director General promises to rejig skills acquisition programme NYSC assures of hitch-free mobilisation process Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin